  "prompt": "What is advice to a man at age 33 who failed at business and earning money, and who still lives with family?",
  "response": "Here's some constructive advice for someone in that situation:\n\n1. Personal Development\n- Don't be too hard on yourself\n- Learn from past business failures\n- View challenges as learning opportunities\n- Stay positive and motivated\n\n2. Career Strategy\n- Assess your skills and strengths\n- Consider additional education/training\n- Explore different career paths\n- Look for stable job opportunities\n- Consider consulting or freelancing\n\n3. Financial Planning\n- Create a realistic budget\n- Start saving, even small amounts\n- Build an emergency fund\n- Reduce unnecessary expenses\n- Consider debt management strategies\n\n4. Skill Enhancement\n- Learn new marketable skills online\n- Take free/affordable courses\n- Develop digital/technical skills\n- Improve communication and networking abilities\n\n5. Entrepreneurial Approach\n- Start small business/side hustle\n- Network with successful entrepreneurs\n- Learn from mentors\n- Be open to different business models\n\n6. Mental Health\n- Seek professional counseling if needed\n- Practice self-compassion\n- Manage stress and anxiety\n- Stay connected with supportive people\n\n7. Personal Goals\n- Set clear, achievable short-term goals\n- Develop a long-term vision\n- Work consistently towards objectives\n- Maintain work-life balance\n\nRemember: Success is a journey, not a destination. Stay persistent and adaptable.",
